==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Simoniacal
<hw>Sim`o*ni"a*cal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to simony; guilty of simony; consisting of simony.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Sim"o*ni`a*cal*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The flagitious profligacy of their lives, and the
<qex>simoniacal</qex> arts by which they grasped at the popedom.</q>
<rj><qau>J. S. Harford.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simonial</ent>⟦br⟧
